comments:
Created 1.4.1932 from the parishes of Bicester Market End, Bicester 
    King's End and Caversfield. See also Table 2, note (c).

Abolished 1.4.1932 and divided between the parishes of Bicester 
    and Chesterton.

Abolished 1.4.1932 and divided between the parishes of Bicester, 
    Ambrosden and Bucknell.

Transferred from Buckinghamshire to Oxfordshire on 20.10.1844. 
    See also Table 2, note (c).

Abolished 1.4.1932 and divided between the parishes of Hardwick 
    with Yelford, Hardwick with Tunsmore and Standlake.

Created 1.4.1932 from the parishes of Tusmore and Hardwick. See 
    also Table 2, note (c).

Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Newton Purcell 
    with Shelswell.

Created 1.4.1932 from the separate parishes of Newton Purcell 
    and Shelswell. See also Table 2, note (c).

Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Newton Purcell 
    with Shelswell.

On 20.10.1844 the part in Buckinghamshire  was transferred to Oxfordshire, so that thereafter Stratton Audley was 
    wholly in Oxfordshire. See also Table 2, note (c).

Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Hardwick with 
    Tusmore.
